programme.title: Fantastic Four
programme.desc: In this hip reboot of the comic-book franchise, a brilliant scientist builds a device that allows users to teleport to an alternate dimension, but an experiment involving it goes wrong and leaves him and his three teammates with unusual superpowers. The quartet are then forced to work together to battle an enemy from their past.

programme.title: George Lopez
programme.sub-title: The Kidney Stays in the Picture
programme.desc: Angie doesn't like how George instructs Max about having a girlfriend. But Max's bed-wetting is indicative of a further problem. Dr. Woodson: Ken Howard. Kristi: Ashly Holloway.

programme.title: Wipeout
programme.desc: A romantic obstacle course is tackled by twelve engaged couples, who will face the Love Boat Launch, the Springivator and a Wedding Cake Testing.

programme.title: Wipeout
programme.sub-title: Blind Date 2.0: This Could Get Ugly Part 1
programme.desc: Each week 24 contestants go head to head through 4 rounds of hilarious obstacle courses.

programme.title: Family Matters
programme.desc: Valentine's Day vignettes tell stories of love involving the Winslows. Kelsey: Kyla Pratt. Oneisha: Mari Morrow. Greta: Tammy Townsend. Richie: Bryton McClure. Eddie: Darius McCrary. Myra: Michelle Thomas.

programme.title: Family Matters
programme.desc: Eddie (Darius McCrary) alters his genes to appear on a game show, unaware that brainiac Urkel is also one of the contestants. Lee: David Ruprecht. Lyle: Monty Hoffman. Maxine: Cherie Johnson. Urkel: Jaleel White. Carl: Reginald VelJohnson.

programme.title: Family Matters
programme.desc: Carl may regret letting Harriette into his poker game with the guys; and Eddie may regret asking Urkel to sub for him as a peanut vendor at the Bears game. Rick: Todd Susman. Zoohair: Iqbal Theba. Willie: Marlon "Chopper" Young.

programme.title: George Lopez
programme.sub-title: A Funeral Brings George to His Niece
programme.desc: Angie's rich former sister-in-law dies and leaves everything to her spoiled 20-year-old daughter, Veronica (Aimee Garcia). But she can't get her money until George---who's the trustee of the will---decides she's mature enough to handle it.

programme.title: George Lopez
programme.sub-title: George Gets Caught in a Powers Play
programme.desc: George decides to teach his rich niece Veronica (Aimee Garcia) a lesson in the value of honest labor by getting her a job at the factory. Trouble is, the men want to do all of her work, and the boss (Mark Tymchyshyn) wants to do something else with her.

programme.title: George Lopez
programme.desc: Andy Garcia guest stars as Angie's brother Ray, a con artist who reappears after five years. Could it have something to do with the fact that his daughter, Veronica (Aimee Garcia), inherited millions? As it happens, Ray wants to help his daughter with her business venture.

programme.title: George Lopez
programme.sub-title: George Helps Ernie See the Cellu-Light
programme.desc: Ernie needs to lose weight or else Mel will fire him, so George plays diet guru. But first he must play psychologist, because Ernie won't admit that he has a problem. Mel: Mark Tymchyshyn.

programme.title: George Lopez
programme.desc: In a crossover episode with "Freddie," Max has struck up an online friendship with Freddie's niece Zoey (Chloe Suazo). George finds out and assumes that "Zoey" is really a pervert. In Chicago, Freddie assumes the same thing about Max.

programme.title: 2 Broke Girls
programme.desc: Caroline is excited to go out on her first date with Bobby, but she gets nervous jitters when she realizes Max will be in charge of the dessert bar solo for the first time. Meanwhile, Sophie and Oleg decide to mix things up and try going out on a date instead of staying in.

programme.title: 2 Broke Girls
programme.desc: Caroline prepares for her third date with Bobby and tries to spice things up by taking a burlesque class. She's accompanied by a reluctant Max, who decides to give up sex in the wake of her breakup with Randy. She also goes golfing with Han.

programme.title: 2 Broke Girls
programme.desc: Caroline tries to make a good impression when she meets Bobby's family at a party, but she isn't prepared when his mother and sisters keep comparing her to his ex-girlfriend. Making things worse, the diner gang decides to tag along.

programme.title: 2 Broke Girls
programme.desc: Han's new therapist suggests that Max needs to confront her "daddy issues" and fear of intimacy, so she reluctantly heads to Rhode Island to track down her birth father with the diner gang in tow. Meanwhile, Oleg gets upset when Sophie asks him to help out around the house.

programme.title: Cleopatra Jones
programme.desc: A female federal narcotics agent is determined to stamp out the world drug trade.

programme.title: Cleopatra Jones and the Casino of Gold
programme.desc: Tamara Dobson returns as the narcotics agent, battling a ruthless casino owner in Hong Kong.

programme.title: The Thirteenth Chair
programme.desc: The friend of a murder victim stages a seance to locate the killer.

programme.title: Freaks
programme.desc: Tod Browning's cult classic about the relationship between a circus "little person" and the beautiful trapeze artist who marries him for his inheritance, but runs afoul of his fellow sideshow colleagues and their code of honor. Genuine circus and carnival performers were cast as the "freaks."

programme.title: Mark of the Vampire
programme.desc: Tod Browning directed this remake of his 1927 silent thriller "London After Midnight," but moved the action to a remote Middle European village, where strange evils stalk the inhabitants and a police inspector teams with an occult expert to investigate.

programme.title: The Devil Doll
programme.desc: Tod Browning's chilling tale of a vengeful, wrongly convicted escapee (Lionel Barrymore) from Devil's Island who opens a "doll" shop of live shrunken humans---who do his dirty work. Browning and Erich von Stroheim scripted.

programme.title: Miracles for Sale
programme.desc: Horror director Tod Browning's final film is a tale about a magician who comes to the aid of a terrified girl who finds herself in the middle of a fraud, murder and people involved with the supernatural.

programme.title: The Leopard Man
programme.desc: After a leopard used in a nightclub act escapes, mysterious murders begin occurring in a quiet New Mexico town.

programme.title: Isle of the Dead
programme.desc: Terror reigns on the citizens of a Greek island besieged by a plague in 1912 during the Balkan Wars.

programme.title: The Body Snatcher
programme.desc: In 19th-century Edinburgh, a brilliant surgeon refines his technique on cadavers supplied by a grave-robbing coachman. As demand rises, so do suspicions about the duo's nighttime activities and the men must turn to murder. Based on a story by Robert Louis Stevenson.

programme.title: Ghost Ship
programme.desc: When a ship captain shows signs of mental breakdown, a young sailor under his command tries to warn the rest of the crew before all their lives are endangered.

programme.title: Martin Scorsese Presents Val Lewton: The Man in the Shadows
programme.desc: A profile of filmmaker Val Lewton (1904-51), who was famous in the 1940s for making affecting, quality horror pictures on a low budget, includes interviews with directors Roger Corman and Kiyoshi Kurosawa, and features clips from "Cat People," "I Walked With a Zombie" and "The Leopard Man."

programme.title: Salt of the Earth
programme.desc: Hispanic mining workers form a union and fight to improve working and living conditions in their New Mexico town. Based on a true story, the film stars mostly nonprofessional actors and people who were involved in the real-life strike.

programme.title: A King in New York
programme.desc: Charles Chaplin wrote and directed this satire in which he plays an exiled European monarch dealing with 1950s American TV, Madison Avenue, rock and roll and plastic surgery. Chaplin's son Michael Chaplin costars as a young boy the king takes in. Because of the filmmaker's inhospitable treatment in the United States, the movie was not released in America until 1973.

programme.title: The Brave One
programme.desc: A story of a Mexican peasant boy and the bull he saves and makes his pet, until the original owner of the animal returns to claim the beast and ship it off to the bullring, where it is pitted against the country's top matador. The film won a Best Story Oscar for Robert Rich, who was actually blacklisted writer Dalton Trumbo.

programme.title: Time Without Pity
programme.desc: An alcoholic writer is in a race against time to find the real culprit behind the murder his estranged adult son has been accused of committing.

programme.title: The Boy with Green Hair
programme.desc: A war orphan's hair changes color to bright green overnight because of battle trauma. He tries to convince the world that war must stop forever, but faces opposition because of his bizarre appearance.

programme.title: Soundies: A Musical History Hosted by Michael Feinstein
programme.desc: A look at soundies (precursors to music videos), which appeared on machines called panorams in the 1940s. Included: clips of Les Paul, Cab Calloway, Louis Jordan, Duke Ellington, Merle Travis and Kay Starr. Also: comments from film historian Leonard Maltin, Hugh Hefner, and musicians George Duke and Wynton Marsalis.

programme.title: The Freshman
programme.desc: A bumbling not-so-big man on a college campus crashes through a collection of classic sight gags in this classic satire of college life.

programme.title: So This Is College
programme.desc: Two football players vie over a pretty coed.

programme.title: College Coach
programme.desc: A science nerd finds new life as a football hero.

programme.title: Hold That Line
programme.desc: The Bowery Boys upset a staid college. Leo Gorcey, Huntz Hall. Biff: John Bromfield. Katie: Mona Knox. Candy: Veda Ann Borg. Directed by William Beaudine.

programme.title: Too Many Girls
programme.desc: Rodgers and Hart's stage hit about college life, brightly transferred to the screen. Lucille Ball, Ann Miller. Clint: Richard Carlson. Jojo: Eddie Bracken. Al: Hal LeRoy. Eileen: Frances Langford. Manuel: Desi Arnaz. Tallulah: Libby Bennett. Fine musical numbers, pleasant cast. George Abbott produced and directed.

programme.title: Good News
programme.desc: Collegiate capering with a football star who won't be able to play in the big game if he doesn't get his grades up and the student-librarian who tutors him, much to the dismay of the campus vamp whom he's dating. The score features the Oscar-nominated "Pass the Peace Pipe," "Lucky in Love," "The Best Things in Life Are Free," "The Varsity Drag" and the title tune.

programme.title: Saturday's Hero
programme.desc: A first-rate college-football drama. John Derek, Donna Reed, Sidney Blackmer, Alexander Knox. From Millard Lampell's novel "The Hero." David Miller directed.

programme.title: Knute Rockne---All American
programme.desc: Biopic about Knute Rockne (1888-1931), with Pat O'Brien as the legendary Notre Dame football player and coach, and Ronald Reagan as the gone-too-soon gridiron great George Gipp. Despite a blitz of macho blustering, don't be surprised if the tears flow during O'Brien's "win just one for the Gipper" speech.

programme.title: The Awful Truth
programme.desc: Best Picture nominee about a bickering couple who are divorcing and go to great lengths to get under one another's skin, including pursuing new dalliances and attempting to sabotage each other's romances. Leo McCarey won a Best Director Oscar.

programme.title: My Favorite Wife
programme.desc: A woman returns home to her husband and their children after being marooned on a desert island for seven years. But she has been declared legally dead, and he now has a second wife.

programme.title: The Philadelphia Story
programme.desc: In this Best Picture nominee, Katharine Hepburn re-creates her Broadway role as a divorced society woman preparing for her wedding while fending off the advances of a magazine reporter and her ex-husband. Playwright Philip Barry's comedy of manners captures "the privileged class enjoying its privileges" and landed Donald Ogden Stewart a Best Screenplay Oscar and James Stewart a Best Actor award as the journalist.

programme.title: It's Alive
programme.desc: A wife who's used an experimental fertility drug gives birth to a horribly mutated homicidal infant.

programme.title: It Lives Again
programme.desc: Sequel to "It's Alive," about three monstrous, murderous babies.

programme.title: The Merry Widow
programme.desc: A playboy prince from a small country is forced to court a wealthy widow in order to ensure that her money stays in their homeland.

programme.title: Screwball Squirrel
programme.desc: A wacky squirrel provokes a slow-witted dog to chase him. Directed by Tex Avery.

programme.title: The Man on the Rock
programme.desc: Historical short tells a story about how a double stood in for Napoleon Bonaparte during his exile while the real emperor escaped and returned to France, only to be killed while trying to visit his son in Austria. Johnny Sheffield, Claude King. An entry in the "MGM Historical Mysteries" series.

programme.title: Over the Andes
programme.desc: A visit to South America includes a stop in the Andes Mountains and Rio de Janeiro.

programme.title: Stage to Chino
programme.desc: A retired postal inspector intercepts the robbery of a stagecoach en route to Chino. He then finds himself caught up in a gold-shipping scam as he goes undercover to investigate it.

programme.title: The New Adventures of Tarzan: Unseen Hands
programme.desc: The jungle warrior Tarzan searches for his missing friend, while helping an officer search for a hidden treasure which becomes dangerous in the wrong hands.

programme.title: Private Buckaroo
programme.desc: Uncle Sam transfers bandleader Harry James from a swank nitery to an Army camp. Andrews Sisters, Dick Foran, Jennifer Holt, Joe E. Lewis, Shemp Howard, Helen Forrest. Many tunes, no story. Edward F. Cline directed.

programme.title: Stranger on the Third Floor
programme.desc: An aspiring journalist testifies he saw a young man at the scene of a brutal killing and the man is sentenced to death. The journalist worries he is responsible for the death of an innocent man and begins his own investigation with his wife, but the duo soon find themselves threatened by a mysterious stranger.

programme.title: Ben-Hur
programme.desc: The Biblical epic re-creates the Nativity, the Crucifixion and a thundering chariot race as it recounts the tale of Jewish prince Judah Ben-Hur, who lives in Judea with his family during the time that Jesus Christ was becoming known for his teachings. The film won 11 Oscars, including Best Picture, Actor (Charlton Heston) and Director (William Wyler).

programme.title: The Dirty Dozen
programme.desc: World War II thriller about an American major who recruits a group of military prisoners for a suicide mission on a French chateau held by top Nazi officers. Since no "normal" GI can be expected to volunteer for this assignment, the "volunteers," serving life sentences, receive the dim promise of getting pardons if they survive.
